ANNOUNCER:
All right, moving into
the junior duo‐trio division,

10:20.841 --> 10:23.445
we have Maddie and Mackenzie
with "Run From Mother."

10:23.445 --> 10:26.218
(applause)

10:26.218 --> 10:29.290
Mackenzie, you had to be
scared to death.

10:29.290 --> 10:31.261
♪ ♪

10:34.200 --> 10:36.471
♪ Hey, little girl,
where do you ♪

10:36.471 --> 10:37.775
♪ Think you're going ♪
(laughing)

10:37.775 --> 10:39.712
♪ You've been trying
to prove yourself ♪

10:39.712 --> 10:42.250
♪ A long, long time ♪

10:42.250 --> 10:43.820
♪ Who are you now ♪

10:43.820 --> 10:46.291
♪ With all those
demons lurking ♪

10:46.291 --> 10:48.563
♪ Getting this far has been ♪

10:48.563 --> 10:50.399
♪ A long, long climb ♪

10:50.399 --> 10:54.374
♪ She ran to the corner to prove
that she wasn't afraid ♪

10:54.374 --> 10:56.846
I can't believe my face
looked like that.

10:56.846 --> 10:58.550
♪ Looking over the bridge
that led to downtown ♪

10:58.550 --> 11:01.221
♪ She took a breath
of the city air ♪

11:01.221 --> 11:03.225
♪ And she had herself ♪

11:03.225 --> 11:06.799
♪ A look around ♪

11:06.799 --> 11:08.970
♪ Brave ♪

11:11.441 --> 11:13.713
♪ Brave ♪

11:15.784 --> 11:17.220
♪ Brave. ♪

11:17.220 --> 11:19.224
(cheering, applause)

11:29.945 --> 11:32.383
When you see somebody every day,
and you're with someone

11:32.383 --> 11:34.655
every day,
you just become like family.

11:34.655 --> 11:36.458
BRYAN: Abby, you used to go
to family dinners

11:36.458 --> 11:37.995
with Melissa
and the kids, right?

11:37.995 --> 11:40.800
Do you remember having them
show off, doing tricks

11:40.800 --> 11:43.305
in restaurants?
I think a lot of my teaching

11:43.305 --> 11:46.077
goes on outside
the classroom.

11:46.077 --> 11:47.446
So, when we're together

11:47.446 --> 11:49.952
and we're having dinner.
And we're in a restaurant

11:49.952 --> 11:53.191
and somebody comes by and says,
"Oh, your girls are so cute."

11:53.191 --> 11:55.296
And I would say, "Mackenzie,
get up. Do a side aerial

11:55.296 --> 11:57.166
"right here.
Go ahead, do it. Maddie,

11:57.166 --> 11:58.268
Maddie, get up.
Do a turn."

11:58.268 --> 12:00.272
I just remember that you
always said to make sure

12:00.272 --> 12:01.609
we have booty shorts
on under our dress

12:01.609 --> 12:03.011
in case you have to show a trick

12:03.011 --> 12:05.784
to someone at a restaurant
or something.

12:05.784 --> 12:06.986
You never know when you're gonna
have to walk on your hands

12:06.986 --> 12:08.923
<i>across the floor,</i>
<i>right Mackenzie?</i>

12:08.923 --> 12:10.760
Who else would
make you do that, though?

12:10.760 --> 12:11.829
Come on.

12:11.829 --> 12:13.198
Your friends
that dance other places,

12:13.198 --> 12:14.702
their dance teachers don't make
them do things like that.

12:14.702 --> 12:16.037
Mm‐mmm.

12:16.037 --> 12:17.708
That's what makes me special.

12:17.708 --> 12:20.479
BRYAN:
Since you guys are such experts
at performing on the spot, let's

12:20.479 --> 12:22.718
play a little game. You're gonna
have to say as many nice things

12:22.718 --> 12:24.555
as you can about your sister
in ten seconds.

12:24.555 --> 12:27.561
Oh!
ABBY LEE:
Or... just blatant things, or

12:27.561 --> 12:28.730
real things?
BRYAN: Really nice.
Really nice things.

12:28.730 --> 12:30.032
Nice things.
I don't want
to do it!

12:30.032 --> 12:31.902
Are they true things or
you're just saying nice words?

12:31.902 --> 12:33.238
No, it's...
True things.
Oh, okay.

12:33.238 --> 12:34.575
You go first.

12:34.575 --> 12:35.777
ABBY LEE: Are you ready?
No.

12:35.777 --> 12:37.013
On your mark,

12:37.013 --> 12:39.150
get set, go!

12:39.150 --> 12:41.321
You're pretty,
you are a good dancer,

12:41.321 --> 12:42.591
you have pretty eyes.

12:45.229 --> 12:47.901
Um, you have good hair,
you have good style...

12:47.901 --> 12:49.437
(buzzing)
Time's up.

12:49.437 --> 12:50.840
I had five.

12:50.840 --> 12:52.043
Can you top her?
Mm‐hmm.

12:52.043 --> 12:54.581
All right, ready?
On your mark, get set, go.

12:54.581 --> 12:58.321
You're very cute, you're funny,
you're hilarious,

12:58.321 --> 13:00.459
you attract boys.
Uh, you're...

13:00.459 --> 13:03.265
you have really good
tumbling tricks, uh, you have

13:03.265 --> 13:05.169
really big eyes,
you have cute hair...

13:05.169 --> 13:06.404
(buzzing)
BRYAN: Time's up.

13:06.404 --> 13:07.841
Seven.
Maddie won.

13:07.841 --> 13:09.343
But she had
more compliments

13:09.343 --> 13:12.249
about me than I had about her,

13:12.249 --> 13:13.653
so I pretty much won.

13:13.653 --> 13:15.990
BRYAN: It's time
for a fan question, Maddie.

13:15.990 --> 13:17.694
Oh, I'll do one.

13:25.042 --> 13:26.612
JILL:
<i>Our plan</i>

13:26.612 --> 13:28.983
is to prove
what we have known all along:

13:28.983 --> 13:32.490
<i>that Maddie gets</i>
<i>extra private time.</i>

13:32.490 --> 13:34.595
We know it's going on,
we need proof.

13:34.595 --> 13:37.399
Get in that studio.
I'll stand watch.

13:40.405 --> 13:42.911
Did you... You got it?
I got it.

13:42.911 --> 13:44.313
Did you get video?
(gasps)
I got video.

13:44.313 --> 13:46.919
CHRISTI:
<i>Maddie's choreography</i>

13:46.919 --> 13:48.455
<i>and Chloe's choreography</i>

13:48.455 --> 13:50.325
were not even
in the same stratosphere.

13:50.325 --> 13:52.229
I thought Chloe's solo
was very technical.

13:52.229 --> 13:53.331
No, it wasn't.

13:53.331 --> 13:55.904
She danced fabulous!
She was amazing!

13:55.904 --> 13:58.609
Her choreography
didn't allow her to win!

13:58.609 --> 14:01.782
I don't really think any of our
privates were very secretive.

14:01.782 --> 14:04.120
I might have had more
privates because my mom

14:04.120 --> 14:06.692
scheduled more privates with us.
And I think that we
weren't the only ones

14:06.692 --> 14:08.529
that got good choreography.
I think everyone

14:08.529 --> 14:10.199
got chor...
good choreography.
No. No.

14:10.199 --> 14:12.537
And maybe it's just the way
you take it and...

14:12.537 --> 14:16.344
There you go. People are given
a step by their dance teacher.

14:16.344 --> 14:17.981
We choreograph a routine.

14:17.981 --> 14:19.952
It's what they do with it,
it's what they

14:19.952 --> 14:22.557
make the choreography look like
when they step on stage.

14:22.557 --> 14:25.530
I think they assumed
you were getting

14:25.530 --> 14:27.534
all these extras because

14:27.534 --> 14:28.903
Melissa and Abby
went to dinner,

14:28.903 --> 14:31.174
or Mackenzie and Maddie get to

14:31.174 --> 14:33.011
do this
and get to do that, because

14:33.011 --> 14:34.480
Melissa helped Abby out.

14:34.480 --> 14:36.484
Whatever it was,
it was always an excuse

14:36.484 --> 14:38.689
so they didn't
have to give you credit

14:38.689 --> 14:41.662
for being great,
hard‐working kids.

14:41.662 --> 14:44.200
BRYAN: Abby, weren't you closer
with Maddie and Mackenzie

14:44.200 --> 14:45.803
than the other girls?

14:45.803 --> 14:47.507
Maddie and Mackenzie and I

14:47.507 --> 14:49.010
share several bonds.

14:49.010 --> 14:50.513
There were
some difficult times

14:50.513 --> 14:52.884
while you two
were at the dance studio.

14:52.884 --> 14:54.287
Their mom and dad
got divorced.

14:54.287 --> 14:56.391
I think that your dancing
kind of protected you,

14:56.391 --> 14:57.459
a little bit, from all that.

14:57.459 --> 14:59.564
Mm‐hmm.
And you
had somewhere else to be

14:59.564 --> 15:00.967
and something
to keep your mind on.

15:00.967 --> 15:04.173
After that, it wasn't long that,
um, my mom got sick.

15:04.173 --> 15:07.479
I think that's
what made us closer.

15:07.479 --> 15:09.283
In those final days

15:09.283 --> 15:10.820
of my mother's life,

15:10.820 --> 15:13.626
Melissa was there every day.

15:13.626 --> 15:17.032
She would always drive me
in her Cadillac car,

15:17.032 --> 15:18.201
and I remember
she would

15:18.201 --> 15:20.038
<i>come to our rehearsals.</i>
<i>Sometimes she'd</i>

15:20.038 --> 15:21.174
<i>bring Baby in the room,</i>
<i>and Baby would</i>

15:21.174 --> 15:22.176
<i>run around when we were</i>

15:22.176 --> 15:23.411
<i>dancing and it was...</i>

15:23.411 --> 15:25.583
it was really fun. And...
And she was really sweet

15:25.583 --> 15:27.119
to all of the girls.
Like, she would

15:27.119 --> 15:30.459
buy us really good presents
for our birthdays,

15:30.459 --> 15:32.764
and she was just
really sweet.

15:32.764 --> 15:34.400
ABBY LEE: Yeah.

15:34.400 --> 15:36.437
<i>My mom wanted</i>
<i>to inspire children</i>

15:36.437 --> 15:38.408
to love being on the stage.

15:38.408 --> 15:40.947
And I think she did that
with both of you.

15:40.947 --> 15:42.216
Mm‐hmm.

15:42.216 --> 15:44.053
Let's take a look
at a clip with Mrs. Miller.

15:44.053 --> 15:45.122
ABBY LEE:
<i>Hi, mom!</i>

15:45.122 --> 15:47.493
Hi, Abby. How are you?
How are you? Good,

15:47.493 --> 15:49.263
good, good.
How are you?

15:49.263 --> 15:52.169
This week, moms,
I might not be there.

15:52.169 --> 15:55.643
As you know,
my mother is dying.

15:55.643 --> 15:59.216
She's not gonna get better.
She's not gonna be cured.

16:06.965 --> 16:08.669
There's some place better.

16:09.871 --> 16:11.575
I think my mom

16:11.575 --> 16:13.144
thought of you two
as her grandchildren

16:13.144 --> 16:15.215
that she never had.

16:15.215 --> 16:16.451
We think of her
as a grandma, too.

16:16.451 --> 16:18.556
She predicted
that you would both be stars.

16:18.556 --> 16:20.626
I know she's watching

16:20.626 --> 16:22.463
every move that you make.

16:22.463 --> 16:24.266
You did something a little bit
unusual at the services.

16:24.266 --> 16:26.972
"Broadway Baby"?

16:26.972 --> 16:28.509
Oh, I remember
my baby cousin went

16:28.509 --> 16:30.580
with my mom to visit
Mrs. Miller,

16:30.580 --> 16:31.615
and the whole time
she was playing

16:31.615 --> 16:33.552
<i>with Broadway Baby.</i>

16:33.552 --> 16:35.288
<i>She thought it was real.</i>
MACKENZIE:
<i>She thought the dog was real.</i>

16:35.288 --> 16:37.861
It was real.
Well, it was, but

16:37.861 --> 16:39.330
it was stuffed.
But the...
What it was...

16:39.330 --> 16:41.400
And she loved that dog.
She kept playing with it.

16:41.400 --> 16:44.808
She was like... Yeah.
She would play
with his nails.

16:44.808 --> 16:47.112
'Cause it sat still for her,
and let her do it.

16:47.112 --> 16:48.414
MADDIE:
Yeah.
That's right. I know.

16:48.414 --> 16:51.254
Broadway Baby's death
was really tough, right?

16:51.254 --> 16:53.692
When she passed,
it was awful. It was

16:53.692 --> 16:56.163
as bad as both my dad
and my mom.

16:56.163 --> 16:57.967
We baby‐sat her
for, like, ten days,

16:57.967 --> 17:00.005
and she lost, like,
six pounds with us.

17:00.005 --> 17:02.142
(laughing)
Because we didn't
feed her Big Macs.

17:02.142 --> 17:03.979
And then when she
went right back

17:03.979 --> 17:05.750
with you,
she gained it all back.

17:05.750 --> 17:07.452
Yeah.

17:07.452 --> 17:09.089
Yeah, I'm sure she did.

17:09.089 --> 17:11.160
Where's Broadway Baby now?

17:11.160 --> 17:13.666
My mom
and my dad's ashes

17:13.666 --> 17:15.803
and my dog,
Broadway Baby,

17:15.803 --> 17:19.276
<i>are in a gorgeous,</i>
<i>gorgeous cemetery</i>

17:19.276 --> 17:20.913
<i>in Miami, Florida.</i>

17:20.913 --> 17:23.017
<i>They are together</i>
<i>in the casket,</i>

17:23.017 --> 17:24.019
in the wall,

17:24.019 --> 17:26.090
and my place is
right next door to them.

17:26.090 --> 17:28.428
Wow.
Yes.

17:28.428 --> 17:29.531
I don't know

17:29.531 --> 17:30.833
if you remember,

17:30.833 --> 17:33.371
but the week
that Broadway Baby passed away,

17:33.371 --> 17:35.743
I did a solo called
"Showing You My Heart," and

17:35.743 --> 17:38.348
it was dedicated
to your dog, so...
(laughs)

17:38.348 --> 17:40.686
I thought I remembered
every routine.

17:40.686 --> 17:42.857
I'm sure when I see it,
I'll remember.
Yeah.

17:42.857 --> 17:46.732
ANNOUNCER:
Up next on stage is Madison
with "Showing You My Heart."

17:46.732 --> 17:48.836
Madison.
(applause)

17:50.506 --> 17:52.510
(piano plays slow,
gentle melody)

17:55.415 --> 17:59.490
♪ I'm showing you my heart ♪

18:01.260 --> 18:05.503
♪ Asking you to love me ♪

18:06.672 --> 18:10.913
♪ I'm showing you my heart ♪

18:10.913 --> 18:17.059
♪ Can you see
without my saying? ♪

18:18.227 --> 18:22.269
♪ I'm showing you my heart ♪

18:22.269 --> 18:27.212
♪ It's here for you. ♪

18:27.212 --> 18:29.684
(song ends,
applause and cheering)

18:29.684 --> 18:31.688
ANNOUNCER:
Maddie would like
everyone to know

18:31.688 --> 18:35.361
that her performance was
dedicated to Broadway Baby.

18:43.812 --> 18:45.983
I was always a star
in my own mind.

18:45.983 --> 18:47.018
(laughs)
Oh, I know.

18:48.087 --> 18:49.624
ABBY LEE:
Wherever we were competing

18:49.624 --> 18:51.293
on the weekend,
when we would get off

18:51.293 --> 18:53.064
<i>the bus and walk in</i>
<i>to the auditorium,</i>

18:53.064 --> 18:55.803
<i>there were hundreds of people,</i>
<i>like, screaming our names.</i>

18:55.803 --> 18:57.372
CROWD (chanting):
Abby! Abby!

18:57.372 --> 18:59.209
(people screaming)

18:59.209 --> 19:01.681
Every week,
there were more people there.

19:01.681 --> 19:04.052
How has being famous
changed Abby?

19:04.052 --> 19:05.823
And be honest. Abby,

19:05.823 --> 19:07.192
tell 'em they
can be honest.

19:07.192 --> 19:09.196
(laughing): I think fame
has really gotten to Abby.

19:09.196 --> 19:10.331
(laughs)

19:10.331 --> 19:11.968
What does that mean?

19:11.968 --> 19:13.371
She goes, "Water!

19:13.371 --> 19:14.373
(snapping) I need water."

19:14.373 --> 19:15.709
I need a water.

19:16.778 --> 19:17.680
Give me... give me a drink.

19:17.680 --> 19:18.749
Can I have my water?

19:20.151 --> 19:22.690
None of that water's cold.
It's all warm.

19:25.696 --> 19:27.533
You yell at a lot
of our crew.

19:27.533 --> 19:28.802
PRODUCER:
You've yelled at me.

19:28.802 --> 19:30.506
This is over,
this is done,

19:30.506 --> 19:32.877
so, find another show,
sweetheart.

19:32.877 --> 19:34.747
Hey, you're not
telling me what to do.

19:34.747 --> 19:35.950
That's gonna
stop right now.

19:35.950 --> 19:37.152
I'm not listening to you.

19:37.152 --> 19:38.387
You are not allowed back here.

19:38.387 --> 19:39.691
MAN:
Yeah, I am.
No, you're not.

19:39.691 --> 19:40.726
ABBY LEE:
The moms don't

19:40.726 --> 19:42.395
rule the dance studio,
you idiot!

19:42.395 --> 19:44.233
They don't!

19:44.233 --> 19:45.836
If every mother walked
into every studio

19:45.836 --> 19:48.709
and did as they damn please,
no one would have a business.

19:48.709 --> 19:50.512
But you don't know anything
about that.

19:50.512 --> 19:52.750
You work for someone else.

19:54.386 --> 19:56.257
Someone has to.
Who's yelling at them?

19:56.257 --> 19:58.094
No one. They're never
gonna learn.
MADDIE: That's right.

19:58.094 --> 19:59.797
BRYAN:
Talk to me

19:59.797 --> 20:01.768
about you guys
becoming a major force

20:01.768 --> 20:02.970
in the dance world.

20:02.970 --> 20:04.106
ABBY LEE:
I think

20:04.106 --> 20:06.443
at the very beginning,
it was

20:06.443 --> 20:10.552
win a week, lose a week,
do pretty well, a so‐so week.

20:10.552 --> 20:13.257
But then it hit a point
where we were winning

20:13.257 --> 20:15.228
week after week
after week, and

20:15.228 --> 20:17.600
that was exciting for me
to watch‐‐ the hard work

20:17.600 --> 20:19.136
come to be
and see what

20:19.136 --> 20:20.806
you guys could do
with those numbers.

20:20.806 --> 20:22.743
Make some noise for...

20:22.743 --> 20:24.012
ANNOUNCER:
Abby Lee Dance Company.

20:24.012 --> 20:26.618
(cheering)

20:26.618 --> 20:30.491
ALL:
Abby Lee Dance Company!

20:30.491 --> 20:32.295
ANNOUNCER 2: Miss Mackenzie
with act number 18.

20:32.295 --> 20:34.667
ANNOUNCER 3: Act number 32,
"Amazing Grace."

20:34.667 --> 20:35.836
ANNOUNCER 4:
"Beautiful Revenge!"

20:35.836 --> 20:38.407
Oh, I love
that dance.

20:38.407 --> 20:40.345
ALL:
Abby Lee Dance Company!

20:40.345 --> 20:43.017
Abby Lee Dance Company!

20:43.017 --> 20:45.154
How many times do you think
we've said that?

20:45.154 --> 20:45.823
Abby Lee...

20:45.823 --> 20:46.725
Abby Lee...

20:46.725 --> 20:49.429
BOTH:
Abby Lee Dance Company!

20:49.429 --> 20:51.400
It's exciting
to win.
Mm‐hmm.

20:51.400 --> 20:52.670
How many people have
accomplished that?

20:52.670 --> 20:55.041
It's great to be able
to look back at that.

20:55.041 --> 20:57.112
Maddie, you were
a huge part of these wins,

20:57.112 --> 20:58.682
because if it wasn't
your solo

20:58.682 --> 21:00.786
winning the overall
high score, it was

21:00.786 --> 21:02.957
usually a group number
that you were featured in.

21:02.957 --> 21:06.296
But Mackenzie,
we owe a lot to you.

21:06.296 --> 21:07.600
Good job, pal.

21:07.600 --> 21:09.236
You were a huge part
of this team because,

21:09.236 --> 21:11.006
without you,
I don't think the girls

21:11.006 --> 21:13.512
would have won quite as often.
Wow.

21:13.512 --> 21:14.680
BRYAN: What do you
say to that?

21:14.680 --> 21:15.849
That's crazy. (laughs)

21:15.849 --> 21:17.152
I wouldn't think
you would have

21:17.152 --> 21:19.189
said that.
Let's take a look

21:19.189 --> 21:21.895
at some of Maddie's emotions and
some of Mackenzie's acro tricks.

21:21.895 --> 21:23.832
♪ ♪

21:23.832 --> 21:26.336
Oh, my gosh.

21:26.336 --> 21:29.276
♪ ♪

21:30.445 --> 21:32.348
(Mackenzie laughs)

21:32.348 --> 21:35.054
♪ ♪

21:45.475 --> 21:47.278
♪ ♪

21:47.278 --> 21:50.151
(laughter)

21:53.625 --> 21:56.296
Oh, that's my baby
bumblebee!

21:56.296 --> 21:59.469
♪ ♪

21:59.469 --> 22:01.039
(laughing)

22:03.144 --> 22:04.580
Holy cow.

22:04.580 --> 22:05.849
Man, oh, man.
MADDIE:
I don't even

22:05.849 --> 22:07.987
remember half those dances
that we did.

22:07.987 --> 22:09.524
That was crazy.
They were
beautiful, though.

22:09.524 --> 22:10.626
The Maddie face.

22:10.626 --> 22:12.128
You're so dramatic.
I cried.

22:12.128 --> 22:13.297
She is. That's...

22:13.297 --> 22:14.700
Why do you think
she's in movies and on TV

22:14.700 --> 22:16.170
and doing all
these other things?

22:16.170 --> 22:17.706
Well, I know.
Because she used
that face.

22:17.706 --> 22:19.577
BRYAN:
At one point,

22:19.577 --> 22:22.248
there was a song writer
that was so inspired by

22:22.248 --> 22:24.019
Maddie's work
that she would write songs

22:24.019 --> 22:25.822
for Maddie to perform to.

